&nbsp;
The 36-year-old would then be thrown out against the cops who would first use the taser but when the man continued to advance, one of the agents exploded a gunshot by hitting the 36-year-old on the left shoulder. The attacker was, therefore, rescued and brought immediately to the Niguarda hospital where the health care workers ascertained how the bullet had not affected vital organs.
&nbsp;
The previous intervention that had led to the denunciation of the 36-year-old Egyptian for robbery and resistance had been carried out outside the station by a patrol of the Italian Army that had requested the intervention of the Polfer. The Egyptian would have robbed a Moroccan citizen who, brought to the hospital in a green code following the attack, had then removed from the emergency room, losing his tracks. The 36-year-old, without precedent, had already been reported photo last 24 April 2024 in Belluno since it requires international protection with approved practice. Previously he had applied to Ascoli, where the practice had been rejected for irreperibility.
